Description: A sherd of micaceous red pottery with pale beige surfaces, probably from some kind of transport-amphora. There are incised lines on the exterior surface, made post-production.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 19
Curator's comments: This fragment is of similar fabric to AES 23763 and GR 2010,5002.29 (and 28). Perhaps all these sherds came from a single vessel.
The Findspot number 19 has been scratched into the object, while the Museum register indicates erroneously "18". EA 23763 and GR 2010.5002.29 (and 28)
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.97, p.114, p.115, p.129, p.208, p.224, pl.66)
